        "\n",
        "## Coding in the Interactive Window (The Console)\n",
        "\n",
        "::: columns\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "When you open VS Code and start a Python Interactive window, it acts like the R Console.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Type code at the bottom prompt.\n",
        "- Press **Shift + Enter** to execute.\n",
        "- Output appears immediately above.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "**Working with Scripts vs. Notebooks**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **.py files:** Pure scripts (like .R files).\n",
        "- **.ipynb files:** Jupyter Notebooks (like Quarto/Rmd). \n",
        "- **Recommendation:** Use Notebooks for this class so you can keep your notes and code together!\n",
        ":::\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## Math calculations in Python\n",
        "\n",
        "Python follows standard order of operations (PEMDAS).\n",
        "\n",
        "::: columns\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"50%\"}"
      ],
      "id": "213d49db"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "10**2  # Note: Power is ** in Python (not ^)\n",
        "3 ** 7\n",
        "6 / 9\n",
        "9 - 43"
      ],
      "id": "6b690ae1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"50%\"}"
      ],
      "id": "83110347"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "4**3 - 2 * 7 + 9 / 2"
      ],
      "id": "f720ac03",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "The equation above is computed as $$4^3 − (2 \\cdot 7) + \\frac{9}{2}$$\n",
