        "\n",
        "## The `.` (The Python equivalent of `$`)\n",
        "\n",
        "- To select a single column in Python, we use `.` or `['']`.\n",
        "- `DataFrame.ColumnName` or `DataFrame['ColumnName']`."
      ],
      "id": "1e260c32"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# These do the same thing\n",
        "print(iris.petal_width)\n",
        "print(iris['petal_width'])"
      ],
      "id": "5559b0c1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
